FBIS3-25193 "drafr028_c_94003" FBIS-AFR-94-028 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Feb 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Says NP Using Forces To Sow Chaos MB0902160594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 1400 GMT 9 Feb 94 MB0902160594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The leader of the ANC [African National Congress], Mr. Nelson Mandela, has accused the National Party [NP] of using elements in the security forces to sow chaos in the country. Speaking at the annual congress of the National Union of Mineworkers in Pretoria, Mr. Mandela said the NP had used the security forces to ensure that SWAPO [South-West African People's Organization] did not get a two-thirds majority in the Namibian election. He said the two batallions used then were now being used to create chaos in South Africa.
